Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves developing strategies for common grounding in dialogue systems. The paper may also be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it deals with improving dialogue systems for better human interaction. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves analyzing and interpreting natural language data.
